An Austin man apologized while unsuccessfully trying to rob two banks, according to an arrest affidavit.

Sean Randall Hunter, 34, was charged with robbery by threat, a second-degree felony punishable by up to 20 years in prison.

Police were notified at 6:01 p.m. Tuesday about a robbery by threat at Chase Bank at 12858 Research Blvd. in Northwest Austin,
